<BLOCK1><TI TOCID="II">ORDER</TI>
<P><BOLD>THIS MOTION,</BOLD> made by the Plaintiff for Summary Judgment, was heard June 20, 2017, at the Court House, 161 Elgin Street, in the City of Ottawa, in the Province of Ontario.</P>
<P><BOLD>ON READING</BOLD> the Motion Records and Facta filed, and on hearing the submissions of counsel for the Plaintiff and counsel for the Defendant,</P>
<P>1. <BOLD>THIS COURT ORDERS</BOLD> that the Plaintiff is entitled to eight (8) weeks' notice of termination of his employment.</P>
<P>2. <BOLD>THIS COURT ORDERS</BOLD> that the Plaintiff is entitled to 26 weeks' severance pay.</P>
<P>3. <BOLD>THIS COURT ORDERS</BOLD> that the Plaintiff is entitled to the contributions to his RRSP, which would otherwise have been made during the eight-week notice period.</P>
<P>4. <BOLD>THIS COURT ORDERS</BOLD> that the Plaintiff's claim for common law reasonable notice of the termination of his employment in the amount of 22 months is dismissed.</P>
<P>5. <BOLD>THIS COURT ORDERS</BOLD> that the Plaintiff's claims for payment or reimbursement of professional fees and other expenses are dismissed.</P>
<P>6. <BOLD>THIS COURT ORDERS</BOLD> that in the event parties are unable to agree upon costs of the motion for summary judgment, they may make written submissions <STRIKE>as follows:</STRIKE> in accordance with paragraph 118 of the March 28, 2018 Ruling on the Motion for Summary Judgment.
<P1><STRIKE>(a) The submissions shall be limited to a maximum of four pages, exclusive of a bill of costs.</STRIKE></P1>
<P1><STRIKE>(b) Written submissions shall comply with Rule 4 of the Rules of Civil Procedure.</STRIKE></P1>
<P1><STRIKE>(c) Hard copies of any case law or other authorities relied on shall be provided with the submissions and shall comply with Rule 4 of the Rules of Civil Procedure with respect to font size;</STRIKE></P1>
<P1><STRIKE>(d) The submissions, the documents referred to therein, and case law and other authorities shall be on single sided pages;</STRIKE></P1>
<P1><STRIKE>(e) Written submissions shall be delivered by 5: 00 p.m. on the twentieth business day following the date on which this Ruling is released; and</STRIKE></P1></P>
<P>Justine Corthorn
<P1><STRIKE>(f) In the event any party wishes to deliver a reply to the costs submissions of the opposing party, the reply submissions shall be delivered by 5:00 p.m. on the twenty-fifth business day following the date on which this Ruling is released. Reply submissions shall comply with paragraph (a) to (d) above.</STRIKE></P1></P>
